							<b>About Us</b>
						</h2>
						<hr class="small">
						<p class="lead"> We as a nation suffer from a college attainment gap. Low-income students face considerable barriers to college awareness, access, and success. And as a post-secondary education has become increasingly important in today's society, large gaps in education achievement still remain between students from low-income families and their high-income peers. <br><br>
						
						Every Spring and Fall Break, we lead a weeklong community service trip to New York City. There, we work with Brooklyn high school students, many of whom are first generation college applicants or come from disadvantaged backgrounds. Trip participants will also have the opportunity to witness inner-city public education and learn about education reform all the way from the policy level to neighborhoods in Brooklyn. <br><br>

						Our core mission is to help these students achieve <b>brighter futures</b> by encouraging and inspiring them to continue their education beyond high school. <br><br>

